deck: Emma Harrow's twin brother and a spider-human hybrid. Because of his animalistic nature, his adoptive father Langford Harrow forced Emma to kill him.
description:
Origin

Adam's mother Melodie was a junkie prostitute who, despite being pregnant at the time, was selling her body for drugs at Cougar Bay, Florida. Picked up by captain Stein, he drugged her and took her to the remote Carribean island of Dr. Langford Harrow. Harrow injected her with a spider serum, which sped up her pregnancy. After several hours, Melodie was about to give birth. Dr. Langford gave her an overdose of sedative, killing Melodie. Cutting her open, Dr. Harrow retrieved a male spider-human hybrid, more spider than human, and a female hybrid who had no outward spiderlike characteristics. Naming her Emma, Langford raised her as his own daughter. The male spider-human hybrid was named Adam and is imprisoned by Langford.

Major Story Arcs

The trouble with Adam

Two years and six months after her birth, Emma has developed into a twenty year old woman. She is plagued by nightmares of death and spiders. Langford discovers Emma displays more and more traits of her spider DNA, such as spinnerets. Unknown to Langford, Emma also has begun hunting for a male to mate with. Paolo, Langford's personal assistent, becomes her first mate. Her mating is interrupted by another spider-human hybrid who has escaped his prison moments earlier. The other hybrid is more spider than human. Langford explained that the other hybrid is Adam, Emma's twin brother. Adam is chased away by Langford.

Adam later kills a visiting photographer on the island. Langford decides then and there that Adam must be killed. Seeing how powerful Adam is, he orders Emma to kill her brother. With Emma under complete hypnotic control of Langford, she kills Adam.
name: Adam Harrow

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

Poachy brings his traveling freakshow to Lonely Street, where he displays his oddities to the nearby residents. During one of his regular showings of the horrible Skunk Ape, the ape escapes, thus forcing The Goon and Franky to hunt it down and capture it. This sparked a poor relationship between Poachy and the Goon.

deck: The brother of Charlie Mudd and the other half of the Mudd Brothers.
description:
Origin

Bill Mudd is the brother of Charlie Mudd, together they make up the duo known as the Mud Brothers. Originally working as thugs for hire, they changed their ways after being beaten in a fight by The Goon. From that point onward they aided the Goon in his fight against the Zombie Priest in order to defend Lonely Street.

Creation

Bill Mudd was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

Drawing On Your Nightmares

Bill and his brother, Charlie, are hired by a mobster known as Salvatore to collect a debt owed by Spider. The duo make their way to Norton's Pub where they find Spider; however, he lies to them and tells them that the Goon is the one they're looking for. They then engage in a brawl with the Goon before they all realize the confusion, but Goon uses his local influence to bring the Mud Brothers to his side. As a display of loyalty, they return to Salvatore and pummel him into unconsciousness.

The Goon Volume Three

Alongside his brother, Bill aids The Goon in defending Lonely Street from zombies and other supernatural creatures. However; one of Goon's allies, Merle, sells information to the Zombie Priest. This information is then used to track down several of Goon's friends, including Bill, who is killed by members of the Zombie Priest's army.

Skills & Abilities

Bill has a rather low intelligence; however, his physiology grants him a low level of superhuman strength.

deck: A supernatural creature who was summoned by the Zombie Priest. After eating the brain of G-Man Smith he obtained his memories.
description:
Origin

The Bog Lurk was a supernatural creature that lived in the swampland/bogs near Lonely Street. He was eventually summoned by the Zombie Priest and forced to eat the brain of G-Man Smith. Doing such gave the Bog Lurk the personality and memories of Smith, causing him to want revenge on The Goon for "killing" him.

Creation

The Bog Lurk was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Two

The Bog Lurk is seen in his swampland before being summoned by the Zombie Priest via a magical incantation. When he arrives at the Zombie Priest's lair he is bound to a table and forced to eat the brain of G-Man Smith, a former ally of the Priest who had information that he needed in order to defeat the Goon. Due to the Bog Lurk's supernatural "powers" so to speak, eating the brain of someone (or something) will transfer the memories and personality of that thing into the Bog Lurk, thus transforming him into a G-Man Smith hybrid. He then attempts to hunt down the Goon to find out why he had killed him, and while he's able to find the Goon he isn't able to best him in a brawl, resulting in the departure of the Bog Lurk from Lonely Street.

Powers & Abilities

The Bog Lurk has the power to absorb the memories and personality of someone (or something) by eating it's brain. It also has a low level of superhuman strength and impressive agility.
name: Bog Lurk

deck: Swearing revenge on her father, Isabel St. Ives became the Nemesis for the sole purpose of killing her immortal father. She was the first person to wear the Nemesis costume.
description:
There have been 3 characters named Nemesis with the same outfit and powers. For the second Nemesis, go to Jane Thorne. For the third Nemesis, go to Nemesis.

Origin

Isabel St. Ives, witnessed her father, a gangster named Deadly Ernest, accidentally killing her mother. She swore to avenge her mother, and used science and magic to create the sword. She was later inspired by the superhero group known as Alpha Flight to become a superhero as well. She made herself a startling costume and named herself Nemesis, hoping to take on her father.

Creation

Isabel St. Ives was created by John Byrne and first appeared in Alpha Flight Vol.1 issue 8 (1984). She was the first person to wear the Nemesis costume.

Major Story Arcs

First Contact

Nemesis finally found herself ready to take on her father as her alter-ego Nemesis. During her assould on Deadly Ernest's house, she by chance assisted Alpha Flight members Aurora and Northstar in their battle with Deadly Ernest and cut her father to pieces, disappearing afterward. It was unknown who the mystrious woman was to both Alpha Flight members and she was not seen again for a long time.

Father Returns

It seemed that Nemesis was never to be seen again. This all changed when her father, Deadly Ernest was revived by Scramble and managed to kill most of the Alpha Flight team. It was then that Nemesis returned, and kept the team alive through the life forces of Ernest's previous victims, long enough for Puck to kill Deadly Ernest again. Nemesis explained her origin to the team-members, but disappeared seemingly for good after that.

Powers and Abilities

Nemesis is an unpowered humans whose abilities were granted by the magic sword.

Equipment and Weapons

Nemesis carries The Onyx Sword. The blade is less than an atom thick in width and is capable of cutting between molecules. The Onyx Sword can cut through almost anything and is indestructible. It also grants the wielder certain powers such as the ability to fly, teleport and absorb life force through the blade.
name: Isabel St. Ives

deck: Jane Thorne was the second person to take on the identity as Nemesis. She first appeared as the leader of Gamma Flight and later on also joined Alpha Flight's ranks.
description:
There have been 3 characters named Nemesis with the same outfit and powers. For the first Nemesis, go to Isabel St. Ives. For the third Nemesis, go to Nemesis.

Origin

Jane Thorne was a young woman whom once led a cult called The Children of the Night. She later became the second Nemesis, and became the leader of the team known as Gamma Flight, the team was created to replace Alpha Flight.

Creation

Jane thorne was created by James D. Hudnall and first appeared in Alpha Flight Vol.1 issue 76 (1989). She was the second person to wear the Nemesis costume, as well as the person whom wore it the longest.

Major Story Arcs

Gamma Flight

She led Gamma Flight and was tasked to replace Alpha Flight. She was a member of the group until it was disbanded. She later became a member of Alpha Flight herself when that team was reinstated. When Carcass got loose, Shaman summoned heroes to kill him; Nemesis was one of those he summoned. She joined the team on a number of missions until Alpha Flight disbanded once more. Her whereabouts at this moment are unknown. A third person has since taken up the mantle of Nemesis.

Powers and Abilities

Nemesis is an unpowered humans whose abilities were granted by the magic sword.

Equipment and Weapons

Nemesis carries The Onyx Sword. The blade is less than an atom thick in width and is capable of cutting between molecules. The Onyx Sword can cut through almost anything and is indestructible. It also grants the wielder certain powers such as the ability to fly, teleport and absorb life force through the blade.

deck: The Mother Corpse is an undead humanoid (zombie) who has the ability to give birth to massive amounts of small, feral children.
description:
Origin

The Mother Corpse was once a human female who was married to a man named Frederick. She became pregnant with his child & named it Michael; however, both her and the child were killed due to complications that occurred during childbirth. Her corpse was dug up by Houstus Grave and brought to the lair of the Zombie Priest who used witchcraft to bring her back to life in an undead form.

Creation

The Mother Corpse was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

Dug up by Houstus Grave & brought back into the mortal world by the Zombie Priest; the Mother Corpse helped bring forth an entire army of feral offspring to aid the Zombie Priest in his fight against the Goon. A spell was then cast on her by The Arab that fused several off her offspring with the spirit of Labrazio to use him in the fight against Goon. After the defeat of Labrazio and the Zombie Priest the spell on the Mother Corpse was removed and she was finally allowed to rest.

Powers & Abilities

It is unknown if she was granted her abilities on resurrection or if it was due to additional spells cast by the Zombie priest & The Arab, but the Mother Corpse had the ability to produce a massive amount of feral, undead offspring that could shape-shift & combine themselves into new and hideous forms. Despite missing the lower half of her torso she was still able to survive, displaying some level of invulnerability/durability.
name: Mother Corpse
